#: ../../Q/quick-and-dirty.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] Describes a :ref:`crock` put together under time or user pressure. "
"Used esp. when you want to convey that you think the fast way might lead to "
"trouble further down the road. \"I can have a quick-and-dirty fix in place "
"tonight, but I'll have to rewrite the whole module to solve the underlying "
"design problem.\" See also :ref:`kluge`\\."
msgstr ""
"[一般的] 時間やユーザーの圧力のもとで急ごしらえされた\\ :ref:`crock`\\ "
"を表す。特に、手早いやり方が後々トラブルにつながるかもしれないと思っていることを伝えたいときに使う。「今夜にはquick-and-"
"dirtyな修正を入れられるが、根本的な設計問題を解決するにはモジュール全体を書き直さなければならないだろう」 \\ :ref:`kluge`\\ "
"も参照。"
